ifetime > 100\nMyr). Finally, ~< 30% (13%) of our sample galaxies are undergoing single\n(multiple) merger(s), they have a projected separation ~< 10 kpc, and the\ntypical mass ratio of our satellites is 1:5 (but ranges between 1:10 and 1:1),\nin agreement with literature results for close pair galaxies.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 28 Jul 2019 20:15:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-14"}
