nthe object. There does not appear to be transient events associated with\npotential exocomets. Each individual star holds its own circumstellar shell and\nthere are no traces of a circumbinary envelope. The combined use of the\ninterferometric and radial velocity data leads to a complete spectrometric and\norbital solution for the binary, the main parameters being: an orbital period\nof 747.6 days, eccentricities of the orbits around the centre of mass 0.25 (HR\n10-A), 0.21 (HR 10-B) and a mass ratio of q=M$_{\\rm B}$/M$_{\\rm A}$=0.72-0.84.\nThe stars are slightly off the main sequence, the binary being $\\sim530$ Myr\nold.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 29 Jul 2019 14:01:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-08-28"}
